        "output": "{'id': 'res_004', 'name': 'David Kim', 'yoe_react': 5, 'yoe_python': 8, 'education': \"MS Computer Science, UC Berkeley (2018). BS Computer Science, Carnegie Mellon University (2016). Thesis: 'GPU-accelerated graph neural networks for recommendation systems'. CMU Dean's List 6/8 semesters.\", 'highlights': \"Senior Software Engineer at Anthropic (2023-present), platform team. Previously Senior MLE at Meta Reality Labs (2020-2023), built recommendation pipeline serving 50M users. Earlier Tech Lead Manager at Google Search (2018-2020), led team of 5 building search ranking inference infrastructure (Python + TensorFlow). Open-source maintainer of pytorch-geometric (3.5k stars). 6 publications at NeurIPS and ICLR, h-index 9. Author of 'Practical ML Systems' (O'Reilly 2022). Looking for a senior IC role at a technically ambitious AI startup.\"}",
